  <text>
    <body>
      <pb n="1" facs="../images/26911_1.png" />
      <div>
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <placeName>Syracuse,</placeName>
            <date when="1854-10-07">Oct. 7, 1854</date>
          </dateline>
          <salute>Dear Friends</salute>
        </opener>
      </div>
      
      <div>
        <p rendition="#indent">
      		The bearee of this<lb />
      		will be <persName ref="psn:peter_still">Peter Still</persName> - one of the<lb />
      		most remarkable of the many<lb />
      		who have recently come out of<lb />
      		the horrid bondage of the American<lb />
      		democratic slave system.<lb />
        </p>
        
        <p rendition="#indent">
      		His story is a peculiar one - as<lb />
      		also the story of his friend <persName ref="psn:seth_conklin">Seth</persName><lb />
      		Conkling. I leave Mr Still to give<lb />
      		his own narrative. You may rely<lb />
      		upon all he tells you - for a<lb />
      		more truthful man does not<lb />
      		live.
        </p>
        
        <p rendition="#indent">
      		He has nearly accomplished<lb />
      		his arduous <choice><corr>undertaking</corr><sic>under taking</sic></choice> - has<lb />
      		raised nearly enough to pay<lb />
      		for the release of his family and<lb />
      		bear the expenses of their removal<lb />
      		to their new home in some<lb />
          one of the nominally free states<lb />
      		of our Union. Do help him to the<lb />
      		residue -
        </p>
          
        <closer>
          <salute>Yours truly</salute>
          <signed><persName ref="psn:samuel_may">Samuel J. May</persName>.</signed>
        </closer>

      </div>
    </body>
